structured.title: Family Coordinates Surgery Lift And Busy Schedule
structured.overview: Jess and family chat informally with the kids about upcoming plans, including a possible trip to Wales and sleepovers, while dealing with school runs and minor car/window issues. Later, the user calls a family member to apologize for a late reply and discuss that her operation has been postponed by a week, but she still expects to recover in time for a lateâ€‘May holiday (including a Cape Town trip). They arrange a concrete plan for the user to give Doug a lift to Llandough Hospital for day surgery under general anesthetic: the user will pick him up around 11:25 and drop him at the correct entrance for a 12:00 arrival, while Dougâ€™s mum will collect him later, with the user on standby as backup. They also discuss the userâ€™s intense current workload with Bible collegeâ€”dissertation, essay on Ezekiel 38, and exams due by early Mayâ€”and how the church is helping by sharing preaching duties. The conversation ends with confirmation that the lift is in the diary and affectionate goodbyes.
